                    <h2>How Can You Implement Seamlessly Online Payments?</h2>
                    <p>Since technology evolved to change our aspects of life, most companies’ payment landscape has posed a tricky area to navigate for any business in the hospitality industry. To a greater extent, this problem ensues because hospitality industry payments conceal an incredibly intricate and grossly regulated process that features the whole industry’s distribution channel, which basically includes a channel manager, a PMS, online travel agent (OTA), or booking engine, and a payment gateway. </p>
                    <p>Each of these distribution chains plays a crucial role in capturing and transferring credit or debit card details before your customers even make their payments. This proves that technology has driven most businesses forward and makes room for the much-needed transition. The following are the three main ways you can ensure your business is prepared for online payment processing. </p>

                    <!-- steps -->
                    <div class="feature-subpage-step">
                        <img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/www.bookingninjas.com/img/feature-subpage-payment-1.jpg" alt="Two-way PMS integration" class="feature-subpage-img__align-left shift-left feature-subpage-box wow fadeInLeft" />
                        <div class="feature-subpage-step__wrap">
                            <div class="feature-subpage-step__top">
                                <span>01</span>
                                <h3>Two-way PMS integration</h3>
                            </div>
                            <p>Property Management System, which has its short form to be PMS, is technically a software application used by property-related businesses, commercial, residential rental owners, logistics, intellectual properties, and many other management-related fields. In a more descriptive sense, we can say the property management system is a digital medium that enhances the management and maintenance of business organizations, legalities, and personnel via a single piece of functional system. </p>
                            <p>Furthermore, PMS is a system solution built to monitor the day-to-day operations of a hospitality accommodation business, private properties, among others. In modern hospitality, this newly-developed genius has made the paper-based methods antiquated. </p>
                            <p>Some PMS comes with an in-built channel manager, booking engine, and a payment gateway. It is completely fine if you cannot lay your hands on a PMS of these features. Just make sure the one you are getting offers integration to these systems because they are highly influential for any hospitality business to get more bookings and increase revenue. </p>
                            <p>With the property management system of these integrations, you can be sure of having all payment information directed from your website or an online travel agent to your front desk for processing. This is as easy as it sounds. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-subpage-step">
                        <img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/www.bookingninjas.com/img/feature-subpage-payment-2.png" alt="Online Booking Engine" class="feature-subpage-img__align-right shift-right wow fadeInRight" />
                        <div class="feature-subpage-step__wrap">
                            <div class="feature-subpage-step__top">
                                <span>02</span>
                                <h3>Online Booking Engine </h3>
                            </div>
                            <p>A booking engine is a system that is integrated into the business’ main website and social media platforms to ensure that guests can book an online reservation without stress. In other words, a booking engine is a software solution that allows business organizations, particularly the ones in the hospitality realm, to sell their rooms via their website or social media platforms, e.g., Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook, etc., your hospitality is listed on. </p>
                            <p>A booking engine is so effective in expanding the customer base since it makes it relatively easier to browse through the available vacancies in the hospitality industry and then make a commission-free direct booking, which is one of the measures taken by renowned business organizations to optimize property’s sales strategy, and ultimately maximize revenue. </p>
                            <p>Making a booking online means your guests have to make an online payment to complete the process, and this is where the booking system that is integrated with a payment gateway comes into play. This booking engine is like an online terminal, tethered with a payment network that authorizes customers’ credit or debit card information to make an instant reservation on the company’s website. </p>
                            <p>Like the PMS, some online booking engines come with a payment gateway already integrated with them. That makes it a lot easier for you; all you have to do is buy and use. Also, you can customize it to make it perfectly fit for the purpose. When considering a system like this for your system, make sure it can handle multiple currencies to give more convenience to guests and capture more bookings. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-subpage-step">
                        <img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/www.bookingninjas.com/img/feature-subpage-payment-3.jpg" alt="Channel Manager" class="feature-subpage-img__align-left shift-left wow fadeInLeft" />
                        <div class="feature-subpage-step__wrap">
                            <div class="feature-subpage-step__top">
                                <span>03</span>
                                <h3>Channel Manager</h3>
                            </div>
                            <p>The channel manager works hand-in-hand with PMS and online booking engines in facilitating online bookings. Online travel agents offer hospitality businesses a different payment structure, which hinges on whether they operate on an agency (pay at check-in) or merchant model (pay upon booking). The merchant method employed by online travel agents features virtual credit cards as the payment method. </p>
                            <p>Employing a channel manager’s services gives you a better chance at capturing more bookings and affords your guests the much-needed convenience. All you need to do is accept payment from the online travel agent, then the guest’s payment and information will be transferred straight to your front desk for processing. </p>
                        </div>
